## Additional Terms for Security Research Content

While the MIT License governs the software and code in this repository, the
following additional terms apply to the security research content (attack
walkthroughs, techniques, and documentation):

1. **Educational Use**: All security research content is provided for
   educational and authorized testing purposes only.

2. **No Malicious Use**: You may not use the content in this repository to
   perform unauthorized attacks against any system, network, or infrastructure.

3. **Attribution**: If you use or adapt content from this repository in your
   own work, presentations, or publications, please provide appropriate
   attribution to this project.

4. **Responsible Disclosure**: Knowledge gained from this repository should be
   used to improve security, not to cause harm. Always practice responsible
   disclosure when discovering real-world vulnerabilities.

These additional terms do not limit the rights granted by the MIT License for
the software components of this repository, but serve as an ethical guideline
for use of the educational content.
